Add explicit metadata to AdditionalityReport so downstream code and the UI know what ordering semantics are in use.

## Changes in web/src/additionality/additionalityAnalysis.ts

Add new type and fields:

  export type AdditionalityOrderingMethod = 'reverse_greedy_target_context';

  export interface AdditionalityReport {
    orderingMethod: AdditionalityOrderingMethod;
    sequenceComplete: boolean;
    // ... existing fields unchanged
  }

- orderingMethod: makes the behavioural change explicit and machine-readable.
- sequenceComplete: true when the full removal loop completed successfully; false for partial runs. This is critical because partial reverse runs represent a suffix near the target, not a valid base→target decomposition.

## Acceptance criteria
- Every successful report includes orderingMethod: 'reverse_greedy_target_context'
- sequenceComplete === true on success, false on partial
- No breaking changes to other existing report fields

Create the post-solve results pipeline that merges solver output and projected overlay rows into a unified ResultContributionRow array. This is the central integration layer.

## New module: web/src/results/resultContributions.ts

### ResultContributionRow type
interface ResultContributionRow {
  metric: "emissions" | "fuel" | "cost";
  year: number;
  value: number;

  sourceKind: "solver" | "overlay";
  sourceId: string;
  sourceLabel: string;

  sectorId: string;
  sectorLabel: string;

  commodityId: string | null;
  costComponent: "conversion" | "commodity" | "carbon" | null;

  overlayId: string | null;
  overlayDomain: ResidualOverlayDomain | null;
}

### Functions

buildSolverContributionRows(request: SolveRequest, result: SolveResult): ResultContributionRow[]
- Extract from existing chartData.ts logic: emissions by sector, fuel by commodity, cost by component
- Solver emissions are in tCO2e (no conversion needed)
- Fuel consumption in PJ (use existing convertFuelConsumptionToPj)
- Cost uses existing logic for conversion/commodity/carbon components

buildOverlayContributionRows(projectedRows: ProjectedOverlayRow[], carbonPriceByYear: Record<string, number>): ResultContributionRow[]
- For each projected overlay row, emit:
  - emissions row: value = (directEnergyEmissionsMtco2e + otherEmissionsMtco2e) * 1_000_000 (convert to tCO2e)
  - sectorId = overlayId, sectorLabel = overlayLabel
  - fuel row (energy_residual only, where commodity is not null and finalEnergyPj > 0): value = finalEnergyPj (PJ)
  - cost rows:
    - commodity component: commodityCostAudm2024
    - conversion component: fixedNonCommodityCostAudm2024
    - carbon component: carbonBillableEmissionsMtco2e * carbonPrice (units cancel to AUD millions)

buildAllContributionRows(request: SolveRequest, result: SolveResult, residualOverlays2025: ResidualOverlayRow[], configuration: ConfigurationDocument): ResultContributionRow[]
- Resolve included overlays from configuration
- Resolve growth rates from active demand preset
- Project overlay rows over configuration years
- Combine solver + overlay contribution rows

### Unit handling
- Solver emissions: tCO2e (no conversion)
- Overlay emissions: MtCO2e in CSV → multiply by 1_000_000 to get tCO2e
- Carbon cost: overlayBillableMtco2e × carbonPrice(AUD/tCO2e) = directly in AUD millions (the 1e6 factors cancel)
- Fuel: PJ throughout

## Acceptance
- Produces correct contribution rows for a test solve result
- Unit conversions are correct
- Overlay rows only appear for included overlays

